        "title": "Unusual output when using Jsoup in Java",
        "body": "<p>I am getting this output when trying to use Jsoup to extract text from Wikipedia:<\/p>\n\n<p>I dont have enough rep to post pictures as I am new to this site but its basically like this: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>[]{k[]q[]f[]d[]d  etc..\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Here is part of my code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void scrapeTopic(String url)\n\n{\n    String html = getUrl(\"http://www.wikipedia.org/\" + url);\n\n\n\n    Document doc = Jsoup.parse(html);\n\n    String contentText = doc.select(\"*\").first().text();\n\n    System.out.println(contentText);\n\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>It appears to get all the information but in the wrong format!<\/p>\n\n<p>I appreciate any help given\nThanks in advance<\/p>\n",
